Preheat your #oven{} to 1/2 tsp @salt{for the pasta}.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then slice into rounds approximately 1cm thick.

Pop the aubergine onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden,
~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and tear it into small pieces. Pat dry with
#kitchen paper{}.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%grams} and bring
back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high
heat. Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} and cook
until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Next, add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams},
@sun-dried tomato paste{25%grams}, @dried oregano{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@water{100%ml}(for the sauce) into the pan.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Bring to the boil, then lower
the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

Preheat your #grill{} to high heat.

Stir the cooked pasta and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%grams}
through the sauce.

Transfer the pasta to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Layer the
roasted aubergine over the top, then scatter over the remaining hard Italian
style cheese and mozzarella.

Once hot, grill the pasta bake until the cheese is golden and bubbling,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Share the chicken and aubergine parmigiana bake between your bowls.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%grams} alongside. Finish by drizzling over the
@balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!